liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: England are batting on here this morning, Stuart Broad resuming on 2 and Anderson on 8. Broad, helmet off, leads Jimmy Anderson (helmet on) down the stairs and then walks through the guard of honour on his own. It's the last time these two will play together - the 138th and final Test of Broad and Anderson in tandem. That's a really nice touch from the Aussies. There is a huge ovation from the crowd, who have not stopped applauding. I imagine the sporting reception will be shelved pretty quickly now as hostilities resume, with a short-ball field in place.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Australia gives Stuart Broad guard of honour

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext:
Another win for the ABC. A Dog's World with Tony Armstrong and ANC News Breakfast are Tony's programs. "Truly didn't think this would happen," he said. "After I was lucky enough to be given the Graham Kennedy Award, I said that we were going to be renegotiating contracts. And I told Justin (Stevens) if on the off chance — he's the big boss — I told him on the off chance if I won this, there would be a renegotiation. 
So mate, my agent's are calling."
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Tony Armstrong wins the Bert Newton Award for Most Popular Presenter

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: This has been a lot closer than I expected. It feels like the Colombians are going at full throttle and the Germans have another gear, but who's to say the South Americans can't keep it up for another 45? No clear cut chances for either side, though you probably would have expected Popp to put away her volley. Plenty of physicality from both sides.
